place_description: Independent coffee shop with breakfast, house-baked pastries & baklava, brick walls & a fireplace.

reviews_data.review_text: Great chill spot, great customer service

I love central coffee with all my heart. Somehow, this has become my go to coffee spot, even though I try others time to time. But I've been here over 30 times. I always get the same thing - iced dirty chai latte & a chocolate chip scone.

Their iced dirty chai cannot compete with others bc they will always take 1st prize. I don't know what it is but it's literally the best thing I've ever tasted. Their chocolate chip scone is mouthwateringly delicious. I've had chocolate chip scones elsewhere, and they've been nothing but disappointing (esp after having theirs).

I'm moving soon & won't be 7 min away from here but you best believe I still will go out of my way to come here.
I like this place, people friendly and service is good.
Decided to go here on my day off and it was quiet and the muffin was soft and delicious. The prices for the coffee and muffin were under $10 even with the tip. Glad I decided to stop by here today.

A great small business coffee.  I love their iced lattes and quiches. The vegan cake was a real treat when I had to eliminate milk and egg from my diet. Really fair prices. Open early if you have a tiny human messing with your preferred sleep schedule

My workmates and I head over to Central Coffee at least once or twice per week to get coffee, breakfast sandwiches, and pastries. The staff is always very helpful and the food is great.  They have tons of options for beverages, teas, coffee, etc.  I usually keep it simple with a light roast drip coffee, a breakfast sandwich, and a chocolate chip croissant to go.  Central coffee is a hidden gem in the East Side if you like the old style cafes like the ones you used to visit in college.  :-)

Decided to try this coffee shop out after a recommendation from a friend. It's located right down the street from my job. Came around 9 am. on a Wednesday, and it was not busy. Parking is very small with about 5 spaces to choose from. I ordered a Hazelnut iced latte with a double espresso shot. It was definitely strong, but I wish it had more flavor. Either way, it was very tasty, and I loved it. I ordered their spinach and Swiss quiche, which was DELICIOUS! & Only for $5, YES, PLEASE! I will definitely be coming back to try out other coffees and pastries. I recommend this little mom and pop coffee shop.

i don't know what changed but the items on the menu are not the same...i asked to make my tea stronger and they just remade the same tea...i love going here but something has changed and i do not like it

I ordered a coffee 30 minutes before their 6 PM closing on a Saturday. Coffee was bitter and sour, undrinkable, and staff was unfriendly, as usual. It's sad because I otherwise like the location and vibe of this place.

I love this place. I come here almost every morning before work and it's the best part of my day. I love the employees (Shye, Chloe, Abigail, Morgan and the rest!) and I absolutely love their espresso here. I've tried a lot of coffee shops in Charlotte and Central by far has the best tasting espresso for drinks and will always be my first choice!

Also, to the negative reviewers who can't get cold foam etc here.....maybe try the starbucks down the street?  This isn't a chain coffee shop, so maybe stick to your chains if your expectation is for small coffee shops to have the same products :)
This was a very nice atmosphere!!!

We stopped to get some coffee while traveling through the Charlotte area and we're very disappointed. I ordered an iced matcha latte and ask for Vanilla cold foam and they said they couldn't make cold foam, what coffee shop can't make cold foam? My husband got the hot chocolate and it was absolutely flavorless. Employees were kind but acted like they hated their jobs.

The young lady who served me was very nice to the customer ahead and went above and beyond to help her. It was my turn and I was not given the same service I clearly wanted some help and some opinions about what would taste good for my drink because I'm not a big coffe drinker. Spent $8 on the drink and hated it she looked annoyed at me and even gave better customer service to my friend who was not a black woman. She then proceeds the leave my cup on the counter while everyone else was handed there drinks in hand. I am a black woman jus to put it out there.

The staff here are very kind and accommodating. It is a calming and small place to get work done or to catch up with friends. I got the 16 oz latte with 1 pump of lavender vanilla syrup and 1 pump of white chocolate syrup. They're both a very nice combination if you have a sweet tooth. I would like to dine in the next time I come!
Great coffee
Fantastic breakfast casserole! The staff is really friendly.  They also have a great chai!!! Cool atmosphere. Great place to get some work done
A really nice, clean, quiet place. Coffee is great, food is good. Friendly staff, quick service. Highly recommend!
No frills, good quality. Friendly staff, and great chai latte.
Solid quiche and coffee, superb pecan pie. Highly recommended.
Coffee was good but biscotti was a bit old/stale.

This place is the heart of the neighborhood. The coffee is great and the casserole on Saturdays is the best.  The staff is incredible. There was a line and they noticed me walk in. They handed me my daily cappuccino as I waited to pay.
Nice environment.  Coffee was delicious.
Great coffee and service
One of the best iced Americanos I've ever had.
Love this place. Great coffee and quiche!
The best Filthy Chai Latte I've had to date. My wife order matcha latte in almond milk  with white mocha. No complaints over here. Don't change your recipe and process. Happy customers from Atlanta!

One of Charlotte's very best coffee shops & one of my personal all-time-favorites. I have eaten more slices of the incredible vegan zucchini bread than could ever be quantified! Nice atmosphere, incredibly kind staff and owners, and superb oat milk lattes!
One of my favorite places to order.
Really pleasant and inviting atmosphere. Hot a coffee and an early grey scone, would recommend!
Very nice place. Great glorious morning muffins.
Cute coffee shop! Good coffee and really good quiche. Cute stickers and merchandise. A good place to sit and study if you can find a seat!
Excellent coffee, but stop letting people park on the street; we have places to be

Ordered a cortado and an Americano...meh, fine, not great. Cortado was too hot, milk was too hot, which burnt the coffee.

Place is kind of messy...boxes out on the floor, supplies stored out front.

I want to give this place a better review but calling it what it is...average.

This is what a coffee shop should be; comfortable, relaxing, a place you can catch up with friends, work on projects or just read. A great neighborhood landmark lacking in pretention, no corporate coffee chain feeling here.
Coffee was great! Cute little spot!

Went to this location today and the cashier had no personality didn't greet me. He acted as though I was bothering him. It's really unfortunate that customer service isn't a priority anymore. Blame it on COVID like everybody else !!!!! Will not be returning. The chocolate croissant I purchased was just threw in the bag not wrapped or anything.

The coffee is pretty good & the staff is nice. This is my local coffee shop but I won't be going back, there are too many inconsistencies with the hours. Usually open until 6pm and they will randomly close at 1pm and the only way to know is if you go there and it is posted on the door.
The sign says because of staffing issues with I understand, however for me I won't go back because I'm tired of walking there and it's closed, just a waste of time.
Great coffee and the atmosphere is so cozy and intimate.
Best coffee shop in town...hands down!!!
My favorite coffee spot in Plaza Midwood. Their oat milk hazelnut latte is the best I've had in CLT. Super chill vibe in a walkable neighborhood
This was a very inviting atmosphere. The staff were very friendly. The coffee was good. I also had a shortbread cookie which was also very good. I definitely recommend this place.

Always looking for a special coffee experience, this place was not it for me. My daughter just found this place. She had been a couple times with hopes that this may be the spot for us when I visit . I had a cortado and zucchini bread. The food surpasses everything else. Especially the staff. I got excited to see that the owners were mountaineers, (I am a mountaineer mom). Yet when ordering and initiating small chat in regards to such. They all seemed unbothered and could care less. It did take me by surprise that EVERYONE that worked there seemed miserable and unhappy . I even supported a second visit , after a 30 min drive , the coffee was good and the service was consistent with just , we could care less if you come or not. So with that being said, we will just take our average of 75.00 week coffee house spending habit elsewhere. Here is a little note to Central Coffee ..Customers still do come first somewhere. So my daughter and I will continue with our quest as it is obviously not there.
Nice little Cool out spot and friendly staff bathroom for paying customers only witch is my cup of tea. Great meet up spot for friends.
Good place to get a nice cup of coffee and something to eat in the morning and not real pricey

Been here a few times this fall. Nice place to get focused work done for a few hours. Wi-Fi. Lighting is more on the dim side, kinda nice. Chill vibe. Try the quiche, coffee, bagels - it's all good. Friendly crew.    Quick service. Note: Best for solo work or 2 people. As of now only one table for a larger group (4-5).
Hip place but my cap. was boiling.  Hate that!
Nice coffee spot in the middle of town
Horrible service, flimsy cups not worth holding coffee, I do not recommend this place to an avid coffee drinker. My first time here and won't be back!
Terrific for catering! Coffee wonderful, baked goods excellent, delivery on time, and owner attentive to every detail!
Tried and true. Nice little coffee shop with great coffee and staff!
Very groovy place. Comfortable and cozy. Good choice of coffee, crossiants, cakes, etc. Totally quaint. Easy pick up and go, or sit and chat. Enjoy. peace.
Always thought it was pretty nice. However, last time there was an eggshell in my sandwich and a hair in my coffee, then to top it off the staff was rude about it.
Double central shorty op op

I love this little coffee shop. It is a short pleasant walk from my daughters' place when I am visiting her.  Everyone is friendly that early in the morning. The coffee is delicious.  I treat myself to a scone or muffin which is also delicious.  It is clean and well organized. A very comfortable, inviting place to sit and have my first, and only, cup of coffee.
Had a blast at the location, the owners were there and we're very accommodating. I also enjoyed getting to know a little bit about the family history of that coffee place. Highly recommend

Lots of coffee shops in this area feel more like bars than Cafes, especially on weekends. This one is almost always much cooler and laid back, and a great place to work or study (and a lot more reasonably priced). Perfect place to upgrade from Starbucks without ruining your wallet, and getting a similar atmosphere.
Amazing!
Amazing coffee, pastries, and breakfast options. I worked here for almost 3 years and it was the best job of my life! I still visit often and never get tired of the zucchini bread!
Pastries and cake were dry, good atmosphere

Got two types of coffee and zucchini bread.

Both types tasted a little burnt, the dark more so than the light, but the zucchini bread was good, and I got a lot of work done.

Nice baristas, too.

I have been supporting central coffee company on Louise Ave for quite a while and recently it has been terrible- the staff and the product. Every time I order it's a wild card. They either take 45 minutes to make 2 lattes (literally 45 mins) and you have to remind them or they make it completely wrong or it's bitter. It's not worth it at all. This time in particular, my shots were sour AND the flavoring that I paid for wasn't in it. I will not be back here.
Nice and quaint atmosphere

I don't know who makes y'all's blueberries scones but they smack. As for the coffee I really like your beans and I also like that you guys just always have dark roast ready. Staff is always polite and quick makes for a really great 2-minute stop on my way to school.

Central coffee is a fantastic spot. Their coffee is top notch, but their baked goods are just as delicious. The atmosphere in here is calm and quiet. Every place these days is so loud, so I enjoy the tranquility here. Keep up the great work Central!
Stopped in while passing through Charlotte. Very good coffee in a nice location!

Every time I give this place another chance I remember why I never come here. Coffee is not good and they mess up my order almost every time. It's also extremely overpriced compared to other shops. Go to summit coffee instead.
Way better than the national brands....
Good, creamy lattes with seasonal flavors. Wish there's a good breakfast menu too :)

Meh, I won't be going back here any time soon. Drinks were ok but ambiance was very poor.

I came in the morning to get my day started and it was stark quiet, no music, person at register didn't greet me. No art on walls. No personality - depressing, actually.

I can make coffee at home...I mean, these are the things that make coffee shops worthwhile. Simple but important.
Favorite coffee spot in the city

I come to Central Coffee Co every so often to treat myself and they always give great customer service and good coffee. I love how clean the place is and the prices are fair. Thank you Shay for the laugh this morning.
Refuse to bow down to stupidity.

Bad customer service!  Shocked
Plus no design inside whatsoever
Really cozy coffee spot for what is turning into a very commercialized SE. Service is great, coffee is greater.
If you can tolerate spicy try the spicy mexican mocha!  Will not disappoint!
As a Cuban, born and raise and lived in Miami, I can said that, coffee here it's good
I am pretty easy when it comes ro my coffee. An Americano is my go to. I added lavender vanilla and a splash of almond milk this time.

The service was fast and the atmosphere was absolutely lovely! Our barista was extremely helpful and patient too. I ordered a cappuccino, chai latte, and iced americano-- all three were some of the best I've ever tasted.

These idiots, for some strange reason, don't take cash. ever. For any reason. even if you have exact change.

What kind of. moron coffee shop refuses cash? Their attitude isn't so hot, either.
Awful service!!!!!!!!!
No service for people breathing with no clothes on the noses? Segregation or..?
Amazing cafe . Totally recommend!
Fun place and coffee very good here. Didn't have a mask but they gave me one.
So I'm at CC right now. The staff is a bit rushed, loud, and their communication could use improvement.
Great place to study after 12pm. People rush the store for drinks and pastries in the am. But afterwards it's a great study environment.

Not educated staff. Rude behavior.
I asked for a long espreso. They gave me short. I said this is not a long espresso and asked barista if he can make a long one. His response was : "this machine cannot make long espresso"
Facts :
1. He didn't tell me that in the first place.
2. The machine CAN make any size of espresso. The barista was clearly lying to me. Bluntly!

However, the coffee was good.
One star because of the as@#SS who work there.
I would not recommend this place!

well, one of few times to be in Charlotte uptown and wanted get a good! coffee. I was very hopeful as the rating is pretty good, but I felt that the coffee (got a cappuccino) was burnt. it smelt bad after the first sip. anyways, not the first coffee shop disappoints me.
They don't take cash .  Just walked there from a few miles and didn't bring my cards.

Be careful when ordering Chai Lattes here. You apparently need to be very clear as I  was very surprised to get a dirty chai this morning when I hate coffee and never asked for coffee in anything. Parking lot is so small there was no point in trying to go back. In route to another place to get the chai I want.
Starbucks WHO?? This place is heavily slept on & this is coming from someone who has been a daily customer of SB for over 10 years, I haven't been back since. I love this place.

No pour over, it's take a time to make it:)instead that a lot of varieties of coffee  with milk or alt.milk, people forgot the taste of real coffee
Bad service
Small shop! Nice coffee shop atmosphere! The ladies were nice! Very small parking lot...
I was in need of a coffee. they made a great cappuccino. thanks for a pleasant experience

This place is incredible! They have great coffee, really reasonable prices, the staff there is always so friendly and welcoming, and they're always super quick at getting us our drinks. My favorite part is actually their food though! They have the best quiche I have ever had, and absolutely incredible zucchini bread. Their other pastries look great too. Someone in that kitchen works magic!
Great coffee
Fave coffee place in south end neighborhood! Has work rooms and great coffee! I recommend the iced matcha latte with vanilla lavender syrup
My home coffee shop for everyday!

Located in the hip south end area. Nice choices of coffee, tea and non-caffeinated drinks. My drink was on the cold side even though it was a steamer. If you want your drink to be hot, please specify so.
Good coffee and drinks. Nice people behind the counter
Amazing little shop. Friendly staff. Great coffee. Scones are delicious. The owners are sweet. Zucchini bread is a must. Go, it will be good.
It's an okay place, my ginger turmeric tea had tea grounds in it as if it wasn't properly filtered though.
Great latte good service! I would come back for a study session.
Coffee was very reasonably priced and tasted great!  Will return.

Central Coffee Company is a family-owned and operated coffee shop in Charlotte, North Carolina. They first opened their shop in Plaza Midwood in May of 2009.  Their main goal is to serve remarkable coffee and fresh food products,   creating an inclusive community atmosphere. They believe that community is so important. Their staff and customers have become not just a community but their family and friends.
They serve coffee roasted by Joe Van Gogh Coffee Roasters, located in Hillsborough, North Carolina,
Joe Van Gogh has placed a lot of emphasis on social, economic, and environmentally responsible ways of producing their roasted coffees. The owners have been to Nicaragua with the company to develop their knowledge of the coffee industry and to learn where the beans come from and to appreciate the process from seed to plant to flower to tree to roasted coffee.
Great coffee!
Small selection likely due to covid. No dine in options but a perfect stop for an iced coffee if you're walking the tram lines in South End.
Had to order at the doorway. Couldn't see the menu or pastries inside.

It's sad. I thought the coffee was going to be much better.  drove out of my way 30min just to try the coffee and on top of that they still require a mask.

Not worth it in southend. Go check out Not Just Coffee or even the coffee at Suffolk.

Literally spent $6 and poured our the coffee.
They can make you coffee smoothies. That's 10 stars for me.

I got a large hot tea which was good but that Pound cake was bussin . It was so good, it tasted like my grandmas. I was not expecting it to be that good. I went to a local bakery that had specialty pound cakes and they are no where near as good
Great coffee...Just found it strange that they do not accept cash.

I ordered the chai latte with lavender syrup. It was good but the cup was half full (as shown in photo which I took as soon as I got in the car) I would have rather had a full drink instead of 6 oz of foam. I also called them about it. The guy who answered said thanks for letting him know. I might go back if they promise to make a full drink.

Update: The owner reached out to me to rectify the situation and I appreciate that more than anything. That's good customer service which is so hard to come by these days. I will be back. Thank you.

Stopped by my  old (1 year obv) fav coffee spot today. Got a sugar free HNut flavoured Latte and it was delic as always! *Central is open* and doing NON dine in service for you. Scones and other bite sizes are available too. I'm told there is a new location on Camden that will open sooner (30-60 days?) than central avenue can which this locale days is later summer. Both baristas were fast, most helpful-I even got the new address written down for lazy ol me- and handed my fav F starbux coffee professionally created! To me at least, #CentralIsBetter !
Central coffee has been my go to for years. Their chocolate chip scone is hands down the best in Charlotte
Coffee is good

Great coffee and breakfast casserole.
Friendly staff.
No cash accepted. We had to wait outside for our order.

I like a bold chai and Central Coffee definitely delivered. I loved the warm, gingerbread flavors. Friends ordered a cold brew and iced mocha and also couldn't wait to go back again. Quick and COVID friendly service too.

I ordered a whole wheat bagel, toasted with cream cheese. I not only had to wait around 10 minutes for this bagel to toast, it came with cream cheese on the side? I'm not sure if this is a Covid restriction but I think it's silly to wait for a bagel to take this amount of time to toast when I was the only patron in the store. I also left the shop, got in my car only to realize I got a plain bagel
Very friendly! Great cold brew & quiche?

By far my most favorite coffee spot in Charlotte! Coffee central provides a wonderful atmosphere and even better customer service. I really enjoy getting to go on a Wednesday when they have a discount on their bags of beans (I keep mine whole but you can have them ground for you!) They have a wide variety to choose from. Their coffee and small breakfast items are wonderful! My personal favs are an iced caramel vanilla latte with almond milk (they have lots of other milk choices!) And ham and cheese quiche! Stop by and see these friendly people you will not be disappointed!
Me dieron el cafe frio
Above average coffee with below average prices, but what really makes this place great are the staff - the girl that served me today was one of the most pleasant people I've ever met.
A little slow but worth the wait. Coffee was great. The girl at the door was so friendly and helpful
Friendly
Wonderful coffee shop with a helpful friendly staff.  Stop in! You won't be disappointed!!
The lavender latter here is soo good. Anytime I'm in South end, I have to stop by.

Good coffee I took I trip to  Peru. This .  and also the customer service was excellent and outstanding they definitely practice covid restriction policy I hopethe business continues do well .They are awesome and I love the coffee

First timer and I am impressed!

Buen servicio, trato de las e.pleadas muy agradablr
Love the coffee and service was great! Can't wait until these times pass because this spot is a VIBE.
Favorite coffee place in all of Charlotte! Fantastic coffee, treats, & service! Everyone here is always so friendly and happy to be at work. Will continue to be a regular here!
Waits too long

This is my absolute favorite coffee shop. Before the world shut down I visited Central Coffee every Sunday with my family after church. I also went there when I needed to do research and enjoyed the coffee and atmosphere very much. I often met friends there and told many people how much I loved Central. They have great coffee, great staff and a fabulous rewards program. I earned many free cups of coffee. When the pandemic hit and they were shut down I really missed the wonderful coffee but found I could order it and have it delivered. Ever since I have enjoyed Central coffee at home and brew the dark roast most mornings. Once they reopened I have been using the Odeko app to order my coffee every Sunday. It is a pretty easy app to use and I can order it ahead of time and by the time I drive to pick up my coffee it is ready fairly quickly. Today I did just that and ended up waiting for over 30 minutes. Customers who came after I arrived and ordered their coffee in person walked out with their cup of joes and I was still standing there waiting. I was livid. I never write reviews but I needed to get this off my chest. I'd like to say I am never going back but I know that isn't the case. I just wish they could have a better system right now.  They also claim to be short staffed which I find hard to believe with the amount of people out of work. Come on CC you can do better!

One of Charlotte's best coffee shops. This location is more spacious than the original on Central Ave. It has a modern vibe and is a good place to work or study. I recommend the zucchini bread! The chai latte is really good too.
Great coffee. Great people. Glad this is a neighborhood staple.
This is a great coffee joint! The staff is always really nice and the drinks are amazing. Definitely try the quiche too - very good!
NC is in phase 3 of COVID and this coffee shop will not serve anyone without a mask... At least provide the customer a mask if you have these mask requirements in phase 3.
They may make the best chai tea in Charlotte
Clean & Cozy
Love this spot, great staff very knowledgeable of coffee related questions. I look forward to grabbing my coffee from here every couple of mornings. Stop in and get nice french pressed coffee!!

Hear me and my father went to eat today we got our scones to go they are above average nice and sweet I would recommend this to people who like scones I personally got the raspberry. My dad got chocolate pretty tasty.

Wrong order and took over 15 minutes... to not get an espresso...

Great place to jump start your incredible day!

Always fast and delicious

we can't wait to see you guys on the other side of this.

nice

nice

will visit soon . Good luck ...

During a recent visit to Charlotte, I was happy to have found such a nice little coffee shop within walking distance of the Airbnb I stayed in. Walking is good for you, but it's even better when you know there's a great cup of coffee at your journey's end!

There was a line each morning I visited, but it moved quickly. Employees were quite friendly, and one even complimented my Dwight Schrute themed RSVLTS shirt! Engaging in genuine, worthwhile small talk is an art that needs to be revived. These folks get it! And this location is also a good spot to catch a Lyft if heading to other points in Charlotte.

Hope to come back soon and maybe spend some more time in the shop, soaking up a bit more of the Charlotte vibe!

Super sweet and charming, really cozy vibe and fantastically balanced coffee. They have great tea, and baked goods too. The folks working have always been nice, and many common allergens are listed and they have multiple dairy and non-dairy milk options for your coffee or tea
Super tasty coffee and great options. Disappointing WiFi, had to leave to go elsewhere to get work done

at last i have discovered a favorite coffee shop in charlotte. spacious, bright, big tables- good place to get some work done and also to chat w some friends. // i had a fudgy vegan brownie (too sugary but still glad to have it). free refill on drip coffee. nice job w this place, everybody

I've only stopped in for a quick coffee and muffin so I don't know much about the vibe. The vanilla latte is great and about $2 cheaper than Starbucks. The morning glory muffin is pretty good. It's basically a carrot cake muffin and it's very filling.
Try the biscotti
Great service however I was expecting some latte art based on some pictures
Coffee is Great, But Women are Hotter Then The Coffee and Perky ..No Pun Attended
OMG the cold brew
I love the place
The place is nice but the location is sketchy

Excellent cappuccino. The blueberry scone was top notch. On the downside, the lighting is too bright, the wall color is terrible, the table tops are plastic. Something feels very unrelaxing about the interior design.
Just FYI about parking @ this location, you cannot park on the street as you will get ticketed but, you are able to park in the lot on the other side of the building by the White Rabbit.
I love small coffee shops, but this one is hands above! Family owned, fresh scones, etc and the best coffee! I got a cold brew and it was amazing  highly recommend
Great vibe.  Clean.  Very good coffee.
Really good coffee, my go to place.
This is the cute little coffee shop my wife and I have always dreamed of finding back in North Carolina. Amazingly tasty, cute and friendly!
The Sumatra blend is divine! Have it brewed in a french press. It takes a few minutes, but it's worth the wait. Very nice and friendly staff.
Excellent coffee, great staff
Very expensive
Great I will be back
Coffee is great! Every one is super friendly

Lots of good seating so you don't feel like you need to rush out. Feels like a nice community coffee shop. Coffee is good. I'd you're staying a while, you can have your coffee in a ceramic mug and save the paper.
Lavender vanilla latte was very good!
Coffee isn't spectacular
Wi-Fi was not accessible. So bring your own hotspot if you plan using this remote worksit

Great coffee and atmosphere.  I gave 3 stars due to the fact that the internet has not worked each time I've been there and I cannot hotspot because I do not get service (Verizon).  Would easily be 5 stars if they had working internet.
Everything about our visit was top notch.
Good coffee

Amazing coffee! My daily morning spot when my husband and I are in town. The quiche is fantastic and the cold brew has set the bar so high, other cold brews fail in comparison. I've recently introduced it to my daughter and nieces and now I have to purchase it to bring back to Ct.

I do not recommend coming here, considering there are so many other options here in Charlotte.

I just moved to Charlotte and so I have been looking around for coffee shops to call home, as I like to find one that is my go-to for when I need to get work done.

I had been working inside for around 3 hours and got up to use the restroom. It required a key from the barista (which is fine). But when I asked, the barista, (who made my coffee!) questioned if I had bought anything in a very unpleasant way. I assured her that yes, I bought a coffee and I just threw it away in the trash can.

I don't write too many negative reviews but again, I do not recommend Central Coffee. Coffee was average, rude baristas, and tiny TINY parking lot with spaces in a super inconvenient arrangement.

How you treat people matters y'all!!
Great coffee! I tired to spicy mocha and it is quite different, but yummy!

This is my favorite coffee shop in Charlotte. I've been coming here for about 8 years, regardless of all the new places springing up and the other options around town. This place has the perfect vibe: It's a neighborhood joint with great coffee and chill staff and zero annoying coffee pretentiousness. Get a Central Shorty. It's a small single shot latte with a hint of vanilla. Anna gets the 2019 Best Shorty Award according to me and verified by an independent 3rd party. FYI.
My French press coffee was the best I'd ever had and our barista gave us a bunch of free vegan chocolate cake.

What a cute and humble little place! The staff was so pleasant from the moment we walked in until the time we left. By watching them work, it was evident they enjoyed being there. Their art work made with chalk on the menu boards was quite impressive. If you like your coffee bold and strong you will like this place. I got a red eye and it had a complete and robust flavor. The quiche was delicious!
The shop is small and limited parking

We were visiting Charlotte, and looking for best coffee in town: couldn't be happier, found Central Coffee, excellent coffee, very friendly staff abd the place is cozy with awesome views of downtown. Glad we came!

I try a new coffee shop every week and today I tried central coffee out! Gentleman working the cashier was so kind, the environment is peaceful and for the first time in weeks, I was given a cappuccino made properly !! Stellar experience. I will definitely be back, soon.
Came here Saturday afternoon, not enough room inside, got to walk out. Cappuccino I ordered was bitter to my taste, than normally. Service was good and friendly.
